# Public docs feature

- Content from Postgres via `$lib/server/services/docs.ts`
- Only `published` documents visible to anonymous visitors; admins see draft preview with banner
- `/docs` redirects to the first category with published docs
- `/docs/category/[id]` lists all published docs in that category (nested tree)
- `/docs/[id]` renders markdown via `$lib/markdown.ts` (marked + DOMPurify) when `contentType` is `markdown`
- Media pages (`contentType` ≠ `markdown`) embed the file at `mediaUrl` via `DocMediaViewer.svelte` (PDF via same-origin `/api/document-media/[id]` proxy, video/audio players, image, Office Online for public HTTPS only); optional markdown notes render below the embed from `content`
- Sidebar groups published docs by category in `+layout.server.ts`; category titles link to `/docs/category/[id]`
- `/docs/[id]` shows a right TOC (page title + markdown H1/H2) at `lg+` via `DocsTableOfContents.svelte`
